  "description": "TNO (Task-Negative Oscillations) is an EEG dataset containing resting-state and task-based electroencephalography recordings. The dataset includes raw EEG data collected during cognitive tasks and resting-state conditions, provided in EEGLAB format (.set/.fdt files) with accompanying metadata and event information in BIDS-compatible formats. This dataset is designed to investigate neural oscillations and their relationship to task engagement and cognitive processing.",
